external_knowledge:
Migration event refers to a unique migration record identified by migration_id;
Entries in this context refer to the records counted for each migration event;
People involved represent the sum of migrants for each migration event.

sql:
SELECT migration_id, COUNT(*) as number_of_records, SUM(number_of_migrants) as total_migrants
FROM migration_records
GROUP BY migration_id;

